{"author":"Joe Oakhart","author_email":"joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com","author_id":"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d","data":{"alias":"depressant-amethyst-wasp","description":"## Why\n\nWith the gated server surface in place (this epic's server-scaffolding story, on which this\n`depends_on`), the audit page itself must render the full per-ticket audit trail an auditor needs:\nticket details plus the plan-review, completion, and code-review panels, navigable across history,\neach review showing its four passes with thresholds.\n\n## What\n\nThe per-ticket audit page (`/ticket/<id>`) rendering, per the researched UX:\n- Left: the ticket's current `show` details (title / status / assignee / description / acceptance\n  criteria).\n- Right: three gate panels — plan review, completion, code review — each with a newest-first ROUND\n  SELECTOR over the retained history (defaulting to the latest round).\n- Each plan/code review round renders the four passes as a read-only vertical stepper: pass-1 full\n  finding list (collapsed-by-default, with rich headers), pass-2 verification per finding, pass-3\n  determination showing priority-vs-threshold (the value, the numeric `block_threshold`, and the\n  decision), pass-4 coaching; findings are traceable across passes by `norm_id`.\n- The completion panel renders the per-criterion PASS record or the FAIL findings.\n- Honest empty / \"not yet run\" states for absent gates; a page-level read-only banner.\n\n## Scope\n\n- `src/rebar/audit/server.py` — add the `/ticket/<id>` route consuming the story-E read layer.\n- New `src/rebar/audit/templates/*.html` (Jinja2) — the page plus panel/stepper partials; inline CSS,\n  no external assets and no JS build step. Each file kept within the module-size policy (< 500 LOC;\n  split partials along real seams, none < 100 LOC).\n\n## Approach rationale\n\nServer-rendered Jinja2 partials (one per panel/pass) keep the page a pure function of the read-layer\ndata with no client-side state or build tooling — appropriate for a read-only, low-traffic audit\nview, and consistent with the reviewbot's server-rendered approach. The two-scope layout (round\nselector for cross-time history, vertical stepper for the fixed four-pass pipeline) follows the\nprior-art UX researched for this feature.\n\n## Compatibility & rollback\n\nAdditive on top of the server-scaffolding story's gated surface; still default-off, loopback-only,\nread-only. Rollback = the epic's flag / extra. No data or schema change.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] The `/ticket/<id>` page renders the ticket details and the plan/completion/code panels; a\n      review with all four passes shows the pass-1 finding list, pass-2 verification, the pass-3\n      value-vs-threshold determination (including the numeric `block_threshold`), and pass-4\n      coaching. Oracle: a live end-to-end test starting the server on a seeded audited ticket and\n      asserting the rendered HTML contains each pass's content and the numeric threshold.\n- [ ] The round selector lists the retained plan- and code-review rounds newest-first and defaults to\n      the latest. Oracle: an E2E test seeding >1 round and asserting the selector contents and the\n      default selection.\n- [ ] A ticket with no code review / no completion verdict shows an explicit \"not yet run\" state, not\n      a blank or an error. Oracle: an E2E test on a plan-review-only ticket.\n- [ ] `make lint && make typecheck && make test` pass.","id":"ff6f-b655-4058-4308","parent_id":"2141-0ba0-5313-48d4","priority":2,"tags":[],"ticket_type":"story","title":"audit per-ticket page (master-detail, four-pass stepper, thresholds, history nav)"},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"CREATE","timestamp":1784067254252229001,"uuid":"2e831226-9959-403a-b436-a2de05e8df0c"}